Class ClusterWheatleyMultibodyMix

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ClusterAbstract

    public class ClusterWheatleyMultibodyMix
extends ClusterWheatleySoftMix
    This class uses Wheatley's recursion approach to calculating all biconnected diagrams for a mixture, but adds in 3-body contributions.

                                   int[] nTypes,
                                   MayerFunction[][] f,
                                   MayerFunctionNonAdditive[][][] fMulti3,
                                   double tol,
                                   boolean nonAddOnly)
        Constructs a cluster capable of handling mixtures of nonadditive molecules.
        Parameters:
        nPoints - total # of molecules
        nTypes - # of molecules of each type
        f - 2D array of pair Mayer functions (0-0, 0-1, 0-2..., 0-n), (1-0, 1-1, 1-2..., 1-n) ... (n-0, n-1, n-2..., n-n)
        fMulti3 - 3D array of 3-body Mayer functions
